---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import ProductCard from '../components/ProductCard.astro'
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Home Backup Power Guide — Generators, Solar & Battery"
  description="Complete guide to home backup power. Covers portable generators, standby generators, solar battery systems, and power banks for every budget and scenario."
>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="threat-hero">
    <div class="hero-img-wrap">
      <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1548438294-1ad5d5f4f063?w=1600&q=80&fit=crop" alt="Home backup power" class="hero-img" />
      <div class="hero-overlay"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="container hero-content">
      <div class="hero-label">Home Protection · Backup Power</div>
      <h1>Home Backup Power — Every Option Explained</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        From a $50 power bank to a $15,000 whole-home standby system, there's a backup
        power solution for every home and budget. Here's how to choose the right one.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href="#compare" class="btn btn-primary">Compare Options</a>
        <a href="#checklist" class="btn btn-secondary">Get the Free Guide</a>
        <a href="#picks" class="btn btn-text">See Top Picks →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Key facts -->
  <div class="key-facts">
    <div class="container facts-row">
      <div class="fact">
        <div class="fact-value">8 days</div>
        <div class="fact-label">Average outage after a major hurricane</div>
      </div>
      <div class="fact-divider"></div>
      <div class="fact">
        <div class="fact-value">$600</div>
        <div class="fact-label">Starting price for a capable portable generator</div>
      </div>
      <div class="fact-divider"></div>
      <div class="fact">
        <div class="fact-value">10 sec</div>
        <div class="fact-label">Standby generator response time after outage</div>
      </div>
      <div class="fact-divider"></div>
      <div class="fact">
        <div class="fact-value">20 feet</div>
        <div class="fact-label">Minimum distance from home (CO safety)</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Tab strip -->
  <nav class="section-tabs">
    <div class="container tabs-row">
      <a href="#compare" class="tab">Compare Options</a>
      <a href="#portable" class="tab">Portable Generators</a>
      <a href="#standby" class="tab">Standby Generators</a>
      <a href="#solar" class="tab">Solar + Battery</a>
      <a href="#powerstations" class="tab">Power Stations</a>
      <a href="#safety" class="tab">Safety</a>
      <a href="#checklist" class="tab">Free Guide</a>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <div class="container page-layout">
    <article class="article">

      <p class="lead">
        A power outage during a storm isn't just an inconvenience — it stops your sump pump,
        spoils your food, disables medical equipment, and leaves you without heat or AC.
        The right backup power system changes all of that. Here's every option, clearly compared.
      </p>

      <div class="part-heading" id="compare">
        <div class="part-number">Part 1</div>
        <h2 class="part-title">Comparing Your Options</h2>
      </div>

      <table class="compare-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Option</th>
            <th>Cost</th>
            <th>Power Output</th>
            <th>Fuel</th>
            <th>Best For</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Power Bank</strong></td>
            <td>$30–$150</td>
            <td>Phones & small devices</td>
            <td>Pre-charged</td>
            <td>Short outages, go-bags</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Power Station</strong></td>
            <td>$300–$3,000</td>
            <td>1,000–3,600Wh</td>
            <td>Pre-charged / solar</td>
            <td>Apartments, quiet neighborhoods</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="row-highlight">
            <td><strong>Portable Generator</strong></td>
            <td>$400–$1,500</td>
            <td>2,000–7,500W</td>
            <td>Gas / propane</td>
            <td>Most homeowners — best value</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Inverter Generator</strong></td>
            <td>$700–$2,000</td>
            <td>1,000–4,500W</td>
            <td>Gas</td>
            <td>Electronics, quiet operation</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Dual Fuel Generator</strong></td>
            <td>$600–$1,500</td>
            <td>3,500–9,500W</td>
            <td>Gas or propane</td>
            <td>Hurricane-prone areas</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Standby Generator</strong></td>
            <td>$5,000–$15,000</td>
            <td>7,500–20,000W</td>
            <td>Natural gas / propane</td>
            <td>Whole-home, automatic, medical</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Solar + Battery</strong></td>
            <td>$10,000–$30,000</td>
            <td>5,000–30,000Wh</td>
            <td>Sun</td>
            <td>Long-term, no fuel dependency</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <div class="callout">
        <strong>For most homeowners:</strong> A 5,000–7,500W dual fuel portable generator ($600–$1,000) is the best balance of power, cost, and flexibility. See our full <a href="/generators">generator buying guide</a> for detailed recommendations.
      </div>

      <div class="part-heading" id="picks">
        <div class="part-number">Part 2</div>
        <h2 class="part-title">Top Picks by Category</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="section-block" id="portable">
        <h2>1. Portable Generators</h2>
        <p>The best choice for most homeowners. Runs on gasoline, requires manual setup outdoors, and provides enough power to run essential circuits during an extended outage. See our <a href="/generators">complete generator guide</a> for a full breakdown.</p>

        <div class="product-row">
          <ProductCard
            name="Champion 7,500W Dual Fuel Generator"
            asin="B07FDQJRBT"
            price="$729"
            store="amazon"
            badge="Top Pick"
            desc="The best all-around portable generator for most homes. 7,500W on gas, 6,750W on propane. Electric start, runs 8 hrs at 50% load."
          />
          <ProductCard
            name="Generac GP6500 6,500W Generator"
            asin="B01IRQMIDI"
            price="$849"
            store="amazon"
            desc="6,500W handles refrigerator, AC, sump pump, and essential circuits. PowerRush technology provides extra motor-starting power."
          />
          <ProductCard
            name="WEN 56200i 2,000W Inverter Generator"
            asin="B07GBKFYQM"
            price="$399"
            store="amazon"
            badge="Budget Pick"
            desc="Quiet, lightweight, and fuel-efficient. Great for essential charging and small appliances. Ideal for apartments or as a backup unit."
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="section-block" id="standby">
        <h2>2. Standby Generators</h2>
        <p>Permanently installed, connected to your gas line, and starts automatically within 10 seconds of a power outage. No action required — your lights come back on while you're asleep. Requires professional installation.</p>

        <div class="product-row product-row-2">
          <ProductCard
            name="Generac 7172 11kW Standby Generator"
            asin="B07GBKFYQM"
            price="$2,699"
            store="amazon"
            badge="Most Popular"
            desc="Right-sized for homes up to 2,500 sq ft. Quieter than larger units, includes automatic transfer switch. Most popular residential standby generator."
          />
          <ProductCard
            name="Generac 7043 22kW Standby Generator"
            asin="B01N9DNOVT"
            price="$4,299"
            store="amazon"
            desc="22kW powers large homes completely. WiFi monitoring via Generac Mobile Link app. Runs on natural gas or LP. Professional installation required."
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="section-block" id="solar">
        <h2>3. Solar + Battery Systems</h2>
        <p>A home solar + battery system (like Tesla Powerwall or Enphase IQ Battery) stores energy from solar panels and provides backup power during outages — silently, automatically, and without fuel. The highest upfront cost but lowest long-term operating cost.</p>

        <h3>How It Works</h3>
        <p>Solar panels charge a battery bank during the day. When the grid goes down, the system automatically switches to battery power. Modern systems can power an average home for 12–24 hours on a full charge — longer with continued solar generation.</p>

        <h3>What It Costs</h3>
        <p>A Tesla Powerwall 3 with installation runs $12,000–$15,000. A full solar + storage system runs $20,000–$40,000 before the 30% federal tax credit. For homes in sun-heavy regions with frequent outages, the economics can make sense over a 10-year horizon.</p>

        <div class="callout callout-blue">
          <strong>Federal tax credit:</strong> The Residential Clean Energy Credit covers 30% of solar + battery installation costs through 2032. A $20,000 system nets a $6,000 tax credit.
        </div>

        <div class="product-row product-row-2">
          <ProductCard
            name="EcoFlow DELTA Pro Ultra Power Station"
            asin="B09GXTD9KH"
            price="$3,699"
            store="amazon"
            badge="Best Home Battery"
            desc="6kWh expandable to 90kWh. Smart home panel integration, solar charging, and whole-home backup capability. No installation required for basic setup."
          />
          <ProductCard
            name="Jackery Explorer 2000 Pro"
            asin="B09JFQBLQT"
            price="$1,599"
            store="amazon"
            desc="2,160Wh capacity, charges to 80% in 2 hours via AC. Solar chainable up to 6 panels. Runs refrigerator for 40+ hours. No CO emissions — safe indoors."
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="section-block" id="powerstations">
        <h2>4. Portable Power Stations</h2>
        <p>Portable power stations are large battery packs that power devices and small appliances silently and without emissions — safe for indoor use. No fuel, no CO risk, no noise. The right choice for apartments, HOA communities, or anyone who can't run a generator.</p>

        <div class="product-row">
          <ProductCard
            name="EcoFlow DELTA 2 (1,024Wh)"
            asin="B0B6ZFKFHZ"
            price="$699"
            store="amazon"
            badge="Best Mid-Size"
            desc="1,024Wh powers a refrigerator for 12+ hours. Charges to 80% in 50 minutes. Expandable with extra battery. Solar charging compatible."
          />
          <ProductCard
            name="Jackery Explorer 1000 Pro"
            asin="B09JFQBLQT"
            price="$799"
            store="amazon"
            desc="1,002Wh with 1,000W output. Charges from 0–80% in 1.8 hours. Handles refrigerator, TV, lights, and phone charging simultaneously."
          />
          <ProductCard
            name="Anker 737 Power Bank (24,000mAh)"
            asin="B09VPHVT2Z"
            price="$89"
            store="amazon"
            badge="Go-Bag Essential"
            desc="Charges an iPhone 6+ times. Two USB-A, one USB-C. The minimum every household should own — keep it charged year-round."
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="section-block" id="safety">
        <h2>5. Generator Safety</h2>

        <div class="callout callout-red">
          <strong>Carbon monoxide kills.</strong> Every year people die running generators indoors. CO is colorless, odorless, and reaches lethal concentrations within minutes in an enclosed space.
        </div>

        <ul class="action-list">
          <li>Never run a generator inside — including garage, basement, or carport with door open</li>
          <li>Position at least 20 feet from windows, doors, and vents</li>
          <li>Install battery-operated CO detectors on every level</li>
          <li>Never refuel while running — let it cool 15 minutes first</li>
          <li>Use a transfer switch — never backfeed into your panel</li>
          <li>Point exhaust away from your home and neighbors</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="product-row product-row-2" style="margin-top: 24px;">
          <ProductCard
            name="Kidde Nighthawk CO Detector"
            asin="B00002N67S"
            price="$34"
            store="amazon"
            badge="Essential"
            desc="Install on every level when running a generator. Battery backup means it works even during a power outage. Plug-in with battery backup."
          />
          <ProductCard
            name="Reliance Controls 31410CRK Transfer Switch Kit"
            asin="B000E1HNZS"
            price="$89"
            store="amazon"
            desc="Safe, code-compliant way to connect your generator to your home's circuits. Much safer than running extension cords throughout your house."
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="checklist-cta" id="checklist">
        <h2>Free Backup Power Planning Guide</h2>
        <p>Calculate your wattage needs, compare fuel options, and get a pre-storm power checklist — all in one download.</p>
        <form class="cta-form" name="power-guide" method="POST" data-netlify="true">
          <input type="hidden" name="form-name" value="power-guide" />
          <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="your@email.com" required />
          <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Send Me the Guide</button>
        </form>
      </div>

    </article>

    <aside class="sidebar">
      <div class="sb-card">
        <h4>On This Page</h4>
        <a href="#compare">Compare Options</a>
        <a href="#portable">Portable Generators</a>
        <a href="#standby">Standby Generators</a>
        <a href="#solar">Solar + Battery</a>
        <a href="#powerstations">Power Stations</a>
        <a href="#safety">Safety</a>
        <a href="#checklist">Free Guide</a>
      </div>

      <div class="sb-card sb-alert">
        <h4>Buy Before the Storm</h4>
        <p>Generators sell out within hours of a named storm. Buy before hurricane season — not when a forecast appears.</p>
      </div>

      <h4 class="sb-section-label">Related Guides</h4>

      <a href="/generators" class="sb-visual-card">
        <div class="sb-visual-img">
          <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1621905251189-08b45d6a269e?w=300&q=80&fit=crop" alt="Generator guide" />
          <div class="sb-visual-overlay"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="sb-visual-label">Generator Buying Guide →</div>
      </a>

      <a href="/hurricanes" class="sb-visual-card">
        <div class="sb-visual-img">
          <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1563089145-599997674d42?w=300&q=80&fit=crop" alt="Hurricane guide" />
          <div class="sb-visual-overlay"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="sb-visual-label">Hurricane Guide →</div>
      </a>

      <a href="/winter-storms" class="sb-visual-card">
        <div class="sb-visual-img">
          <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1511131341194-24e2eeeebb09?w=300&q=80&fit=crop" alt="Winter storms" />
          <div class="sb-visual-overlay"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="sb-visual-label">Winter Storm Guide →</div>
      </a>

      <div class="sb-card">
        <h4>Quick Wattage Guide</h4>
        <p style="font-size:0.82rem; color:var(--text-mid); margin-bottom:10px;">Running watts for common appliances:</p>
        <div class="quick-calc">
          <div class="calc-row"><span>Refrigerator</span><span>400W</span></div>
          <div class="calc-row"><span>Window AC</span><span>1,200W</span></div>
          <div class="calc-row"><span>Sump pump</span><span>800W</span></div>
          <div class="calc-row"><span>Lights + devices</span><span>300W</span></div>
          <div class="calc-row calc-total"><span>Typical total</span><span>~5,500W</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </aside>

  </div>

</BaseLayout>

<script>
  const sections = ['compare','portable','standby','solar','powerstations','safety','checklist']
  const tabs = document.querySelectorAll('.section-tabs .tab')
  const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
    entries.forEach(entry => {
      if (entry.isIntersecting) {
        tabs.forEach(t => t.classList.remove('active'))
        const activeTab = document.querySelector(`.tab[href="#${entry.target.id}"]`)
        if (activeTab) activeTab.classList.add('active')
      }
    })
  }, { rootMargin: '-20% 0px -70% 0px' })
  sections.forEach(id => { const el = document.getElementById(id); if (el) observer.observe(el) })
</script>

<style>
  .threat-hero { position: relative; height: 480px; display: flex; align-items: center; overflow: hidden; }
  .hero-img-wrap { position: absolute; inset: 0; z-index: 0; }
  .hero-img { width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; object-position: center; }
  .hero-overlay { position: absolute; inset: 0; background: linear-gradient(to right, rgba(13,35,56,0.92) 0%, rgba(13,35,56,0.65) 60%, rgba(13,35,56,0.3) 100%); }
  .hero-content { position: relative; z-index: 1; max-width: 640px; color: white; }
  .hero-label { font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; color: #A8CEDF; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .hero-content h1 { color: white; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .hero-sub { font-size: 1.05rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.8); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 32px; max-width: 560px; }
  .hero-actions { display: flex; gap: 14px; align-items: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .btn-text { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.75); font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 500; text-decoration: none; transition: color 0.15s; }
  .btn-text:hover { color: white; text-decoration: none; }

  .key-facts { background: var(--off-white); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 24px 0; }
  .facts-row { display: flex; align-items: center; }
  .fact { flex: 1; padding: 0 32px; }
  .fact:first-child { padding-left: 0; }
  .fact-value { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--navy); margin-bottom: 3px; }
  .fact-label { font-size: 0.78rem; color: var(--text-light); }
  .fact-divider { width: 2px; height: 36px; background: var(--border); flex-shrink: 0; }

  .section-tabs { background: white; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border); position: sticky; top: 68px; z-index: 90; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.06); }
  .tabs-row { display: flex; overflow-x: auto; scrollbar-width: none; }
  .tabs-row::-webkit-scrollbar { display: none; }
  .tab { font-size: 0.82rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--text-mid); padding: 14px 20px; white-space: nowrap; text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 3px solid transparent; margin-bottom: -2px; transition: all 0.15s; border-right: 1.5px solid var(--border); }
  .tab:last-child { border-right: none; }
  .tab:hover { color: var(--sky); background: var(--sky-light); text-decoration: none; }
  .tab.active { color: var(--sky); border-bottom-color: var(--sky); font-weight: 600; background: var(--sky-light); }

  .page-layout { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 280px; gap: 56px; padding-top: 48px; padding-bottom: 96px; align-items: start; }
  .lead { font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--text-mid); margin-bottom: 32px; }
  .article p { color: #333; line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .article h3 { margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: var(--navy); }

  .part-heading { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 16px; margin: 48px 0 24px; padding-bottom: 16px; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--navy); scroll-margin-top: 140px; }
  .part-number { background: var(--navy); color: white; font-size: 0.72rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; padding: 4px 10px; border-radius: 4px; white-space: nowrap; }
  .part-title { font-size: 1.4rem; color: var(--navy); margin: 0; }

  .section-block { margin-top: 48px; padding-top: 48px; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); scroll-margin-top: 140px; }
  .section-block h2 { color: var(--navy); margin-bottom: 20px; font-size: 1.4rem; }

  .compare-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 24px 0; font-size: 0.88rem; }
  .compare-table th { background: var(--navy); color: white; padding: 10px 14px; text-align: left; font-weight: 600; }
  .compare-table td { padding: 10px 14px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .compare-table tr:hover td { background: var(--sky-light); }
  .row-highlight td { background: var(--sky-light); font-weight: 500; }

  .callout { background: var(--orange-bg); border-left: 3px solid var(--orange); border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0; padding: 14px 18px; margin: 24px 0; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.6; color: #5a3010; }
  .callout-red { background: #FDF0EF; border-color: #C0392B; color: #5a1010; }
  .callout-blue { background: var(--sky-light); border-color: var(--sky); color: var(--navy); }

  .product-row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 16px; margin-top: 20px; }
  .product-row-2 { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }

  .action-list { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 20px 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; }
  .action-list li { padding: 10px 14px 10px 38px; background: var(--off-white); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 5px; font-size: 0.9rem; position: relative; }
  .action-list li::before { content: "⚠"; position: absolute; left: 12px; color: #C0392B; }

  .checklist-cta { margin-top: 56px; padding: 40px; background: var(--sky-light); border: 1px solid #B8D8EE; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid var(--sky); scroll-margin-top: 140px; }
  .checklist-cta h2 { font-size: 1.3rem; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .checklist-cta p { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-mid); margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .cta-form { display: flex; gap: 10px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .cta-form input { padding: 10px 14px; border: 1.5px solid var(--border); border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.9rem; min-width: 240px; font-family: var(--font-sans); }

  .sidebar { position: sticky; top: 120px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 16px; }
  .sb-card { background: white; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 20px; }
  .sb-card h4 { font-size: 0.72rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--text-light); margin-bottom: 14px; font-weight: 600; }
  .sb-card a { display: block; font-size: 0.85rem; padding: 7px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #f0f4f7; color: var(--sky); }
  .sb-card a:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .sb-card p { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-mid); line-height: 1.5; }
  .sb-alert { border-top: 3px solid var(--orange); }
  .sb-alert h4 { color: var(--orange); }
  .sb-ctu { background: var(--off-white); }
  .sb-section-label { font-size: 0.72rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--text-light); font-weight: 600; padding: 0 4px; }
  .sb-visual-card { display: block; border-radius: 8px; overflow: hidden; border: 1px solid var(--border); text-decoration: none; transition: transform 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s; }
  .sb-visual-card:hover { transform: translateY(-2px); box-shadow: 0 6px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); text-decoration: none; }
  .sb-visual-img { position: relative; height: 90px; overflow: hidden; }
  .sb-visual-img img { width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; transition: transform 0.3s; }
  .sb-visual-card:hover .sb-visual-img img { transform: scale(1.05); }
  .sb-visual-overlay { position: absolute; inset: 0; background: rgba(13,35,56,0.45); }
  .sb-visual-label { background: var(--navy); color: white; font-size: 0.82rem; font-weight: 600; padding: 10px 14px; }
  .quick-calc { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 6px; }
  .calc-row { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--text-mid); padding: 4px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #f0f4f7; }
  .calc-total { font-weight: 700; color: var(--navy); border-bottom: none; padding-top: 8px; }
</style>